article.headline: E. Kentucky 72, Murray St. 66
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Mike Rose scored 24 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to a 72-66 win Thursday night over Murray State in overtime. Rose scored 20 points in the second half, including a three-pointer at the buzzer to send the game into overtime. Rose added a three-pointer in overtime to complete the Colonels' comeback. Julian Mascoll followed Rose with 16 points for Eastern (6-2), with 14 of those coming in the second half. Jamaal Douglas chipped in with 11. The Racers (3-7) trailed 55-52 with two minutes left, but scored six in a row for a 58-55 lead with three seconds left, before Rose's three-pointer at the buzzer-forced overtime. Murray held a 40-28 lead with 17 minutes left, but Eastern used a 25-8 run to turn the 12-point deficit into a 53-48 lead with 5:12 remaining. Mascoll and Rose combined for 18 points. The Racers broke a 14-14 tie with a 17-5 run that made the score 31-19 with 2:57 left in the first half. Murray guard Tyler Holloway, who scored 13 points in the half, scored 10 of those during the Racers' spree. Eastern, which shot just 33 percent in the opening half, didn't score a field goal in the final 12 minutes of the half and managed six points, all from the free-throw line. Shawn Witherspoon scored 18 and Holloway added 16 and Bruce Carter added 12 for the Racers.
